snippet.textDisplay: MEDICAL ERROR - yo, Dr Mike - I don't think platelets are actually considered WBCs since they come from the megakaryoblast --> megakaryocyte lineage. Also, platelets are much smaller than either RBCs (6-8 micrometers) or WBCs (12-15 micrometers) - hence, depicted as children. Love your channel, BTW!  - Dr Puck

snippet.textDisplay:
YESSSSS CELLS AT WORK!!!!!!!!! ♥♥♥ Just watch the whole series. It's so worth it. Macrophage-san is my favorite, and someday I will cosplay her!

Episode 3 - Influenza goes into Macrophages and Naive T Cells
Episode 4 - Food Poisoning goes into Eosinophils
Episode 7 - Cancer Cell (no explanation needed)
Episode 8 - Circulation (again, no explanation needed)
Episode 12 & 13 - Hemorrhagic Shock goes into soooooo much, a two-parter, super intense!

Those would be my top 5 anyways. But seriously, they're all so good, and it teaches so much! I'm hoping that they release more in 2020, but I'm guessing they're waiting on the manga (which I need to find and read).
